Class HammingDist

java.lang.Object
HammingDist
public class HammingDist extends Object
Reads in the file in order to parse and find and store the given vehicle numbers. Uses these values to then perform operations, and find the amount of differences (HammingDist), between two given vehicles.
Version:
1
Author:
Diego Cifuentes

    • HammingDist

      public HammingDist​(String string, String string2)
      Calls the readFile method, assigns the vehicles to their given vehicle numbers (string and string2) and then calls other methods where they will be compared and have their HammingDists returned. Checks if both vehicles are the same, if so reverses the second one. Assigns these HammingDist values to their respective variables to be stored. Uses these to help print out the given statements correctly.
      Parameters:
      string - A given vehicle number
      string2 - A second given vehicle number

  • Method Details

    • readFile

      public void readFile()
      Reads in the given file, stored each line first into the fileLines array, then searches for the vehicle numbers and parses them from the fileLines array and stored them into the vehicles array. Expands both array when needed.

      Returns:

    • hammingComparison

      public int hammingComparison​(String vehicle, int differences)
      Uses similar logic to the prior method, but in this case we are looking for other instances that have the same HammingDists.
      Parameters:
      vehicle - The vehicle being compared
      differences - The amount of differences found
      Returns:
      returns the amount of vehicle numbers with the same amount of differences.
